  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/91dd78bde3d7d1457847e8e522e81320122263d2" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:15.025ex; height:6.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle {\frac {|\nu -\mu |}{\sigma }}\leq {\sqrt {\frac {3}{5}}}}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>where | . | is the <a href="/wiki/Absolute_value" title="Absolute value">absolute value</a>.
</p><p>In 2020, Bernard, Kazzi, and Vanduffel generalized the previous inequality by deriving the maximum distance between the symmetric quantile average <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle {\frac {q_{\alpha }+q_{(1-\alpha )}}{2}}}">
